---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader, CardTitle } from '../../../components/ui/Card';
import { CodeBlock } from '../../../components/ui/CodeBlock';
import { Alert, AlertTitle, AlertDescription } from '../../../components/ui/Alert';
---

<BaseLayout title="POLLN & LOG Mathematics - SuperInstance.AI Documentation">

  <section class="section bg-gradient-to-b from-white to-gray-50">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <div class="animate-fade-in">
        <div class="mb-6">
          <a href="/docs" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 flex items-center">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7" />
            </svg>
            Back to Documentation
          </a>
        </div>

        <h1 class="heading-1 mb-6">
          POLLN & LOG Mathematics: The Geometry of Spreadsheet AI
        </h1>

        <p class="text-body max-w-3xl mb-10">
          Discover the mathematical foundations behind POLLN (Pattern-Oriented Local Ledger Notation)
          and LOG (Ledger-Orienting-Graph) systems. Learn how geometric tensor mathematics
          transforms spreadsheet computations into elegant, scalable operations.
        </p>

        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 mb-16">
          <div class="bg-primary-50 rounded-lg px-4 py-2">
            <span class="text-sm font-medium text-primary-700">Reading time: 15 minutes</span>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-accent-50 rounded-lg px-4 py-2">
            <span class="text-sm font-medium text-accent-700">Level: Advanced</span>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-secondary-50 rounded-lg px-4 py-2">
            <span class="text-sm font-medium text-secondary-700">Prerequisites: High school geometry, basic algebra</span>
          </div>
        </div>      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-16">

        <!-- Introduction to POLLN -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="heading-2 mb-6">Understanding POLLN: Pattern-Oriented Local Ledger Notation</h2>

          <p class="text-body mb-6">
            POLLN reimagines how data flows through spreadsheets by treating each cell as a
            pattern-oriented ledger. Instead of simple value stores, cells become pattern
            recognition engines that maintain their own computational history.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-indigo-50 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-3">The POLLN Axioms</h3>
            <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-blue-800">
              <li>Every cell IS a ledger</li>
              <li>Every ledger IS a pattern</li>
              <li>Every pattern IS a transformation</li>
              <li>Every transformation IS a local optimization</li>
            </ol>          </div>

          <h3 class="heading-3 mb-4">The POLLN Method: S = (O, D, T, Φ)</h3>
          <p class="text-body mb-4">
            POLLN represents data as a 4-tuple where meaning emerges from geometric relationships:
          </p>

          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
            <Card>
              <CardHeader>
                <CardTitle>Origin (O)</CardTitle>
              </CardHeader>
              <CardContent>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">The geometric center of meaning</p>
                <CodeBlock code={`Origin: (x₀, y₀, z₀)
Where ideas crystallize into form`} lang="javascript" />
              </CardContent>
            </Card>

            <Card>
              <CardHeader>
                <CardTitle>Data (D)</CardTitle>
              </CardHeader>
              <CardContent>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">Encoded as geometric tensors</p>
                <CodeBlock code={`Data: ∑ᵢ₌₁ⁿ wᵢ × Tᵢ
Weighted tensor decomposition`} lang="javascript" />
              </CardContent>
            </Card>

            <Card>
              <CardHeader>
                <CardTitle>Transformation (T)</CardTitle>
              </CardHeader>
              <CardContent>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">Geometric operations on tensors</p>
                <CodeBlock code={`Transform: T → T' via G × T
G = geometric operator`} lang="javascript" />
              </CardContent>
            </Card>

            <Card>
              <CardHeader>
                <CardTitle>Flow (Φ)</CardTitle>
              </CardHeader>
              <CardContent>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-2">Pattern propagation energy</p>
                <CodeBlock code={`Flow: Φ = ∇ × P
P = pattern potential field`} lang="javascript" />
              </CardContent>
            </Card>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- LOG System -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="heading-2 mb-6">LOG: Ledger-Orienting-Graph System</h2>

          <p class="text-body mb-6">
            LOG (formerly Ledger-Organizing Graph) transforms into <strong>Ledger-Orienting-Graph</strong>,
            emphasizing higher-dimensional orientation that abstracts mathematical operations into geometric intuition.
          </p>

          <Alert type="info">
            <AlertTitle>Geometric Insight</AlertTitle>
            <AlertDescription>
              LOG tensors embed geometric properties for mathematical precalculations through reality-bending tensor constructs.
              By compressing universe properties into tensors, coordinate changes make mathematics trivial.
            </AlertDescription>
          </Alert>

          <h3 class="heading-3 mb-4">LOG Tensor Geometry</h3>

          <div class="space-y-6 mb-6">
            <div class="bg-gray-900 text-gray-100 rounded-lg p-4 font-mono text-sm overflow-x-auto">
              <div class="text-green-400">// Traditional tensor transformation</div>
              <div>T'_{μν} = Λ_{μ}^{α} Λ_{ν}^{β} T_{αβ}</div>
              <div class="text-blue-400 mt-4">// LOG tensor with embedded geometry</div>
              <div>ℒ_{μν} = {T_{μν}, G_{μν}, C_{μν}}</div>
              <div>Where:</div>
              <div class="ml-4">T_{μν} = Data tensor</div>
              <div class="ml-4">G_{μν} = Geometric properties</div>
              <div class="ml-4">C_{μν} = Confidence coefficients</div>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-purple-50 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-purple-900 mb-3">The Power of Pre-geometry</h4>
              <p class="text-purple-800 mb-2">
                LOG tensors don't just store data—they anticipate transformations by encoding geometric
                relationships directly.
              </p>
              <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-4 font-mono text-sm mb-2">
                <div># Example: Pythagorean theorem pre-encoded</div>
                <div>ℒ_{ii} = {(3, 4, 5), {right-triangle}, 1.0}</div>
                <div># Outcome: Instant hypotenuse calculation</div>
                <div>c = √(a² + b²) = immediate</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3 class="heading-3 mb-4">Higher-Dimensional Orientation</h3>
          <p class="text-body mb-4">
            LOG's "Ledger-Orienting" aspect handles dimensionality through permutation logic:
          </p>

          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
            <div class="bg-indigo-50 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-indigo-900 mb-3">Permutation Logic</h4>
              <p class="text-indigo-800 text-sm mb-3">
                Abstracting higher-dimensional orientations through set theory
              </p>
              <CodeBlock code={`For n dimensions:
\u{1}! orientations = n! × 2^{n-1}
\u{1}! LOG maps: σ ∈ S → O(σ)
Where σ is permutation, O is orientation`} lang="javascript" />
            </div>

            <div class="bg-teal-50 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-teal-900 mb-3">Sphere Packing → Platonic Solids</h4>
              <p class="text-teal-800 text-sm mb-3">
                Geometric compression through optimal spacing
              </p>
              <CodeBlock code={`LOG encoding:
Pack(3D) → Platonic relations
Tetrahedron: 4 vertices
Octahedron: 6 vertices
cube: 8 vertices
coordinates = compact tensor`} lang="javascript" />
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Pythagorean Geometric Tensors -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="heading-2 mb-6">Pythagorean Geometric Tensors</h2>

          <p class="text-body mb-6">
            Compass-and-straightedge construction mathematics become powerful because they add
            single words to describe shapes from higher abstraction than any single view can see.
          </p>

          <Alert type="success">
            <AlertTitle>Mathematical Principle</AlertTitle>
            <AlertDescription>
              Whole number right triangles create "easy snaps" for calculation: 3-4-5 gives 36.87°,
              5-12-13 gives 22.62°, 8-15-17 gives 28.07°—these are 2D analogs of Platonic solids in 3D.
            </AlertDescription>
          </Alert>

          <div class="bg-yellow-50 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-yellow-900 mb-3">The Pythagorean "Snap" Principle</h3>
            <p class="text-yellow-800 mb-4">
              Certain angle/triangle combinations snap together like magnets, making computation trivial:
            </p>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
              <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
                <div class="font-mono text-lg text-yellow-900">3-4-5</div>
                <div class="text-sm text-yellow-700">36.87°</div>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
                <div class="font-mono text-lg text-yellow-900">5-12-13</div>
                <div class="text-sm text-yellow-700">22.62°</div>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
                <div class="font-mono text-lg text-yellow-900">8-15-17</div>
                <div class="text-sm text-yellow-700">28.07°</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3 class="heading-3 mb-4">LOG Tensor Implementation</h3>

          <CodeBlock code={`// LOG tensor with embedded Pythagorean properties
struct LOGT {
  tensor: T_{μν},
  vertices: [(3,0), (0,4), (0,0)],  // Right triangle
  angles: {36.87°, 53.13°, 90.00°},
  stabilize: false  // Rotation invariant
}

// Pre-calculated properties
cos(36.87°) = 4/5 = 0.8
tan(36.87°) = 3/4 = 0.75
sin(53.13°) = 4/5 = 0.8

// Tensor operation becomes trivial
rotate(LOGT, θ) =
  if(θ ∈ {0°, 36.87°, 53.13°, 90°, ...}) {
    return pre_computed[θ]
  }`} lang="javascript" />

          <div class="mt-6 bg-gray-900 text-gray-100 rounded-lg p-4 font-mono text-sm overflow-x-auto">
            <div class="text-green-400">// Example: LOG-powered vector calculation</div>
            <div class="text-blue-400 mt-2">// Before: Standard computation</div>
            <div>vec_length = √(x² + y²)</div>
            <div class="text-red-400 mt-2">// Requires: 2 multiplications, 1 addition, 1 sqrt</div>
            <div class="text-blue-400 mt-4">// After: LOG tensor lookup</div>
            <div>vec_length = ℒ(x, y).cached_length</div>
            <div class="text-green-400 mt-2">// Performance: O(1) lookup</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Practical Applications -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="heading-2 mb-6">Practical Applications in Spreadsheets</h2>

          <p class="text-body mb-6">
            POLLN-LOG mathematics enable powerful spreadsheet operations previously impossible:
          </p>

          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
            <Card hover>
              <CardHeader>
                <CardTitle>Geometric Visualization</CardTitle>
              </CardHeader>
              <CardContent>
                <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mb-3">
                  Automatic shape recognition in data patterns
                </p>
                <CodeBlock code={`A1: [[1,2], [3,4], [5,6]]
// SuperInstance recognizes:
// Linear relationship slope = 2
// Geometric pattern = line in 2D
// Confidence = 100%`} lang="javascript" />
              </CardContent>
            </Card>

            <Card hover>
              <CardHeader>
                <CardTitle>Predictive Analytics</CardTitle>
              </CardHeader>
              <CardContent>
                <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mb-3">
                  LOG tensors predict based on embedded patterns
                </p>
                <CodeBlock code={`B1: Sales data [Q1, Q2, Q3]
// LOG analysis:
// Seasonal pattern detected
// Tensor: ℒ(props, momentum, trend)
// Prediction: Q4 = Q3 × 1.08`} lang="javascript" />
              </CardContent>
            </Card>

            <Card hover>
              <CardHeader>
                <CardTitle>Confidence Scoring</CardTitle>
              </CardHeader>
              <CardContent>
                <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mb-3">
                  Geometric confidence through tensor stability
                </p>
                <CodeBlock code={`C1: Forecast result
// Confidence cascade:
// Data quality: 0.85
// Pattern match: 0.92
// Tensor stability: 0.78
// Overall: 0.85 (HIGH)`} lang="javascript" />
              </CardContent>
            </Card>

            <Card hover>
              <CardHeader>
                <CardTitle>Multi-dimensional Analysis</CardTitle>
              </CardHeader>
              <CardContent>
                <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mb-3">
                  Automatic dimensionality detection
                </p>
                <CodeBlock code={`D1: Dataset analysis
// POLLN dimensions:
// Categorical: on/off
// Numerical: temperature
// Temporal: timestamp
// Spatial: coordinates
// All unified through ℒ(μν)`} lang="javascript" />
              </CardContent>
            </Card>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-primary-500 to-accent-500 rounded-2xl p-8 text-white">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Next Steps in Your Mathematics Journey</h3>
            <p class="text-lg mb-6 opacity-90">
              Ready to apply POLLN-LOG mathematics in your spreadsheets?
            </p>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
              <a href="/docs/tutorials/geometric-tensors" class="bg-white/10 hover:bg-white/20 rounded-lg p-4 transition-colors">
                <div class="font-medium mb-2">Tensor Tutorial</div>
                <div class="text-sm opacity-75">Build your first LOG tensors</div>
              </a>
              <a href="/docs/research/pythagorean-primes" class="bg-white/10 hover:bg-white/20 rounded-lg p-4 transition-colors">
                <div class="font-medium mb-2">Prime Number Geometry</div>
                <div class="text-sm opacity-75">Explore number patterns</div>
              </a>
              <a href="/docs/calculators/tensor-generator" class="bg-white/10 hover:bg-white/20 rounded-lg p-4 transition-colors">
                <div class="font-medium mb-2">Tensor Calculator</div>
                <div class="text-sm opacity-75">Generate custom LOG tensors</div
              ></a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Advanced Reading -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="heading-2 mb-6">Deep Dive References</h2>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
            <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Mathematical Foundations</h3>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-600">
                <li><a href="#" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700">Tile Algebra Formal Specification</a></li>
                <li><a href="#" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700">Confidence Cascade Mathematics</a></li>
                <li><a href="#" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700">Rate-Based Change Mechanics</a></li>
                <li><a href="#" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700">ORIGIN-CENTRIC Data Systems</a></li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h3 class="font-semibold mb-3">Research Papers</h3>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-600">
                <li><a href="#" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700">"Pythagorean Geometric Tensors" (2024)</a></li>
                <li><a href="#" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700">"SuperInstance Type Systems" (2024)</a></li>
                <li><a href="#" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700">"Tile Algebra and Composition" (2024)</a></li>
                <li><a href="#" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700">"LOG Tensor Geometric Compression" (2024)</a></li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>